    <h2>Introduction: Finding Your Strength Sweet Spot</h2>
    <p>If you've been using nicotine pouches for a while, you know the feeling: your regular pouch just doesn't hit the way it used to. Tolerance is real, and it's time to step up to something stronger. But jumping straight to a 25mg monster pouch might be overkill — that's where the 10–20mg range becomes your new best friend.</p>
    <p>This guide explores the best strong nicotine pouches available in 2026, focusing on the Goldilocks zone of strength: powerful enough to satisfy experienced users, but measured enough to avoid overwhelming side effects.</p>

    <h2>What Counts as "Strong"? Understanding the 10–20mg Range</h2>
    <p>Nicotine strength isn't as simple as the mg number on the tin. Three factors determine how hard a pouch hits:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Nicotine concentration:</strong> 10–20mg per pouch is the defined range here — roughly double a regular pouch (3–7mg)</li>
        <li><strong>Moisture content:</strong> Wetter pouches release nicotine faster; drier ones deliver a slower, longer-lasting sensation</li>
        <li><strong>pH (alkalinity):</strong> Higher pH increases nicotine bioavailability, so even a 12mg pouch with high pH can feel as strong as a 15mg pouch with lower pH</li>
    </ul>

