    <h2>Safety First: Using Strong Nicotine Pouches Responsibly</h2>
    <div style="background: #fef2f2; border: 2px solid #ef4444; border-radius: 12px; padding: 24px; margin: 32px 0;">
        <h3 style="color: #dc2626; margin-top: 0;">Important Safety Information</h3>
        <p>Strong nicotine pouches are <strong>not for beginners</strong>. If you're new to nicotine, start with regular strength (3–7mg) and only progress to strong options after weeks of consistent use.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Tolerance builds fast:</strong> Your body adapts within 1–2 weeks at a higher strength. Rotate between strengths or brands</li>
            <li><strong>Watch for side effects:</strong> Nicotine overuse can cause nausea, dizziness, headaches, or anxiety. If you experience these, switch to a lower strength immediately</li>
            <li><strong>Don't mix strengths:</strong> Using a 20mg pouch after a 10mg pouch multiplies the effect. Space them out by at least 30 minutes</li>
            <li><strong>Stay hydrated:</strong> Nicotine is a diuretic; drink plenty of water</li>
            <li><strong>Pregnant/breastfeeding?</strong> Avoid nicotine entirely</li>
            <li><strong>Heart conditions or hypertension:</strong> Consult your doctor before using strong nicotine products</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <h3>I'm using regular strength pouches. Can I jump straight to 15mg?</h3>
    <p>We'd recommend starting at 10–12mg first. Jumping directly to 15mg from regular (3–7mg) doubles your nicotine intake and increases the risk of side effects. Spend a week or two at 10–12mg to let your body adapt. <a href="/blog/how-to-choose-your-strength">Read our strength selector for more guidance</a>.</p>

    <h3>Why do some 12mg pouches feel stronger than 15mg pouches?</h3>
    <p>Perceived strength depends on format, moisture, and pH — not just the mg number. A wet, high-pH 12mg pouch can deliver nicotine faster and more intensely than a dry, low-pH 15mg pouch. This is why testing multiple brands is important.</p>

    <h3>Is it safe to use strong pouches every day?</h3>
    <p>It's <em>possible</em> but not ideal. Daily use of 15–20mg pouches creates physical dependence quickly. We recommend rotating strengths and taking 1–2 days off per week. <a href="/blog/nicotine-pouch-side-effects">Learn more about managing side effects</a>.</p>

    <h3>What's the difference between "Extra Strong" and "Strong"?</h3>
    <p>There's no universal standard. "Extra Strong" typically means 11–14mg, whilst "Strong" can mean 10–13mg. Always check the mg content on the tin rather than relying on labels.</p>

    <h3>I'm getting side effects. What should I do?</h3>
    <p>Switch to a lower strength immediately — drop to 10mg or even back to regular (5–7mg). Stay hydrated and avoid caffeine for a few hours. If nausea, dizziness, or chest pain persist, stop using nicotine and see a doctor. <a href="/blog/nicotine-pouch-side-effects">Detailed side effect information here</a>.</p>

    <h2>Final Thoughts: Strong Pouches Done Right</h2>
    <p>The 10–20mg range offers a serious nicotine experience without the extreme risks of 25mg+ products. Our top pick for most users is <strong>White Fox Full Charge (16.5mg)</strong> — it balances strength, flavour consistency, and quality — but the best strong pouch is the one that feels right <em>for you</em>.</p>
    <p>Start with our top recommendations, rotate between strengths to manage tolerance, and always listen to your body.</p>

